result.execSummary:
Keldrick Demon Jenkins Jr was found not guilty on all charges in this case. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Keldrick Demon Jenkins Jr is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
At the hour of 3:51 pm the jury returned and, by their foreperson, brought in a verdict of NOT GUILTY which was then read.  

"We, the jury, find the defendant, Keldrick Jenkins Jr, NOT GUILTY of Possession of a Firearm Contrary to Injunction, as charged in COUNT 1 of the Information."

Court discharged the jury.  Verdict received and filed.  At the hour of 3:56 pm jury dismissed.

Court granted defense motion for judgment on the verdict.  Court ordered entry of judgment of acquittal.  Bail to be refunded to whoever posted it.  Court orders exhibits withdrawn.
